WEBVTT

00:02.964 --> 00:04.473
WOMAN: Previously on "Freakish"...

00:04.474 --> 00:06.308
I got bit.

00:06.309 --> 00:07.601
MAN: Keyword?

00:07.602 --> 00:09.144
Flashpoint Zulu.

00:09.145 --> 00:10.937
MAN: Welcome back, Zulu.

00:10.938 --> 00:13.065
Grover will do anything
he can to save her.

00:13.066 --> 00:15.400
That's exactly why we can't trust him.

00:15.401 --> 00:17.202
[snarls]

00:19.936 --> 00:21.012
[beep]

00:22.200 --> 00:24.034
Um, my battery is almost out,

00:24.035 --> 00:26.568
so I'm making this message

00:26.593 --> 00:28.114
for Mom and Papa and...

00:30.625 --> 00:32.793
and Ninny, if you find this first,

00:32.794 --> 00:34.146
which you always do.

00:35.939 --> 00:37.552
It's been two days.

00:38.224 --> 00:40.052
We're still trapped in the school.

00:40.426 --> 00:42.344
There's no sign of help.

00:42.740 --> 00:43.762
We don't know who's out there.

00:43.763 --> 00:45.804
We haven't made contact with anyone yet.

00:46.413 --> 00:47.982
We're doing our best,

00:48.007 --> 00:49.960
but I don't know how long we can last.

00:53.171 --> 00:54.353
Dad...

00:56.359 --> 00:58.661
I wish we spent more time together.

00:59.654 --> 01:01.224
Some of that was on me.

01:01.823 --> 01:03.404
And Mom...

01:05.868 --> 01:07.387
what can I say?

01:07.870 --> 01:10.012
I guess I'm just a disappointment.

01:13.084 --> 01:16.765
First failed diet, first election lost,

01:17.755 --> 01:20.036
first teen pregnancy.

01:26.180 --> 01:28.014
I just thought you should know.

01:28.015 --> 01:29.996
<i>[eerie music]</i>

01:30.020 --> 01:33.565
Synced & corrected by <font color="#0080ff">king</font><font color="#0000ff">louis</font><font color="#0000a0">xx</font>
www.addic7ed.com

01:33.590 --> 01:39.060
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:41.112 --> 01:44.322
Noodle, are you insane?

01:44.323 --> 01:45.991
I'm going crazy, man.

01:46.016 --> 01:47.211
I just need normal.

01:49.245 --> 01:51.663
You're shooting bricks.
Looks pretty normal to me.

01:51.664 --> 01:53.331
Oh, really? Think so?

01:53.332 --> 01:56.209
Come on, one time.
Let's run it, me and you.

01:56.210 --> 01:57.711
I'm about to break your ankles.

01:57.712 --> 01:59.421
This is not the time, bro.

01:59.422 --> 02:01.047
Whoa.

02:01.048 --> 02:03.467
- You'll never beat me.
- Ohh!

02:03.468 --> 02:04.952
Ever in your life.

02:07.889 --> 02:09.347
Whoo.

02:09.348 --> 02:12.392
<i>[tense music]</i>

02:12.393 --> 02:14.644
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:14.645 --> 02:15.869
Mary?

02:17.000 --> 02:23.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:27.950 --> 02:28.950
[snarls]

02:28.951 --> 02:30.991
[grunts]

02:53.976 --> 02:56.520
[snarling]

02:56.521 --> 02:57.672
Mary.

02:58.648 --> 03:00.440
It's me, it's Grover.

03:00.441 --> 03:02.339
Mary, it's your brother.

03:03.110 --> 03:04.820
Mary, please!

03:04.821 --> 03:06.144
- WOMAN: Grover?
- [snarls]

03:07.114 --> 03:08.615
No.

03:08.616 --> 03:10.561
No, no, no, no, no!

03:15.030 --> 03:16.444
Whoo.

03:17.911 --> 03:19.411
Beginner's luck.

03:19.436 --> 03:21.020
I'll see you in an hour.

03:21.045 --> 03:22.629
What you mean? We're not done.

03:22.630 --> 03:24.172
Gotta go check on Zoey.

03:24.173 --> 03:26.716
Oh, so my love's
not good enough for you?

03:26.717 --> 03:27.677
[kisses]

03:27.678 --> 03:30.720
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

03:30.721 --> 03:32.764
[doors creaking]

03:32.765 --> 03:40.765
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:49.323 --> 03:51.658
Shit. Grover.

03:51.659 --> 03:53.118
I thought you were that.

03:53.119 --> 03:54.786
What was that?

03:54.787 --> 03:58.081
It was Mary. She's turned.

03:58.082 --> 03:59.499
Come on.

03:59.500 --> 04:01.376
And there's five seconds
left in the game.

04:01.377 --> 04:03.503
The inbound pass to Deveraux.

04:03.504 --> 04:05.005
He passes it to Noodle.

04:05.006 --> 04:06.339
Can Noodle do it?

04:06.340 --> 04:07.841
For the title.

04:07.842 --> 04:09.676
Can it be?

04:09.701 --> 04:11.904
<i>[tense music]</i>

04:11.929 --> 04:13.471
[rattling]

04:13.472 --> 04:21.471
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:30.489 --> 04:35.494
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:39.624 --> 04:42.792
- Everyone grab a weapon.
- You said the north stairs?

04:42.793 --> 04:44.127
- North?
- Yeah.

04:44.128 --> 04:46.796
Those go one flight up,
two flights down.

04:46.797 --> 04:49.883
Shit. She could be anywhere.

04:49.884 --> 04:51.088
Here.

04:53.012 --> 04:55.096
All right, well, that's seven.
We're missing one.

04:55.097 --> 04:57.098
Noodle. Yo, he's in the gym.

04:57.099 --> 04:58.642
- He doesn't know.
- Yeah, go.

04:58.643 --> 05:00.352
Zoey, you... never mind.

05:00.353 --> 05:03.688
Okay, Diesel, Natalie, second floor.

05:03.689 --> 05:04.773
Come on.

05:04.774 --> 05:08.276
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

05:08.277 --> 05:09.737
Mary?

05:10.571 --> 05:11.847
Mary?

05:13.706 --> 05:16.076
Mary, everything is gonna be okay.

05:16.077 --> 05:20.747
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:20.748 --> 05:22.241
I can't do this.

05:23.459 --> 05:26.523
I have a baby in here.
I'm like a walking goddamn Happy Meal.

05:27.254 --> 05:29.078
So why was it a mistake?

05:29.103 --> 05:30.433
What?

05:31.008 --> 05:33.510
Having a baby, you said
it was a mistake, right?

05:33.511 --> 05:35.428
Making a baby was the mistake.

05:35.429 --> 05:37.389
Who's the guy?

05:37.390 --> 05:38.682
Does it matter?

05:38.683 --> 05:40.433
You even know?

05:40.434 --> 05:41.977
No.

05:41.978 --> 05:44.854
I'm a total slut. Yes, of course I know.

05:44.879 --> 05:47.918
It was Model UN in Philly.
I was Denmark. He was Greece.

05:48.859 --> 05:50.860
So what did he say about the baby?

05:50.861 --> 05:52.551
He doesn't know.

05:53.489 --> 05:54.948
You didn't even tell him?

05:54.949 --> 05:56.658
Hey, where are you going with this?

05:57.228 --> 05:58.838
Right here.

05:59.036 --> 06:00.036
Sorry.

06:00.037 --> 06:01.913
Diesel, what are you doing?

06:01.914 --> 06:04.332
No, Diesel!

06:04.845 --> 06:06.751
You're right, you can't do this.

06:06.752 --> 06:08.820
- It's not safe.
- Diesel!

06:12.299 --> 06:15.343
<i>[tense music]</i>

06:15.344 --> 06:19.222
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:19.223 --> 06:20.716
Looks clear.

06:23.477 --> 06:25.478
We can't trust Grover.

06:25.479 --> 06:27.058
Not anymore.

06:28.149 --> 06:29.691
He cares too much.

06:29.692 --> 06:31.943
Isn't that why we should trust him?

06:31.944 --> 06:34.283
[scoffs] Don't go bleeding heart on me.

06:34.308 --> 06:35.822
It's not like you.

06:35.823 --> 06:37.518
You don't know me.

06:38.075 --> 06:39.502
I know enough.

06:40.696 --> 06:42.822
Don't worry,
neither one of us are saints.

06:42.847 --> 06:44.831
And what is that supposed to mean?

06:44.832 --> 06:45.832
[chuckles]

06:45.833 --> 06:47.355
[loud bang]

06:47.380 --> 06:48.847
Okay.

06:49.962 --> 06:51.629
Stay close.

06:51.630 --> 06:53.673
Who's saving who?

06:53.674 --> 06:55.842
Hmm, "whom."

06:55.843 --> 06:57.343
"Saving whom."

06:57.344 --> 07:05.344
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:10.399 --> 07:11.900
[all gasp]

07:11.901 --> 07:13.818
I'm sorry.
I didn't know it was you guys.

07:13.819 --> 07:15.689
Any sign of her?

07:16.489 --> 07:17.556
No.

07:18.657 --> 07:21.653
- Cafeteria's clear.
- I'll take this floor.

07:21.678 --> 07:23.119
We'll take upstairs.

07:28.292 --> 07:30.835
<i>[tense music]</i>

07:30.836 --> 07:32.420
- Noodle!
- Are you insane?

07:32.421 --> 07:33.755
Shut up.

07:33.756 --> 07:36.049
There's two of us. We have an advantage.

07:36.050 --> 07:38.218
- Noodle!
- Shut up.

07:38.219 --> 07:39.928
Why don't you start handing out menus?

07:39.929 --> 07:42.388
Look, you gotta relax.
It's nothing, okay?

07:42.389 --> 07:44.029
- [distant banging]
- That was not nothing.

07:44.054 --> 07:45.809
Come here, Zoey. Look at me.

07:45.810 --> 07:50.563
We don't have time. We got this, okay?

07:50.564 --> 07:52.417
Come on, grab my hand.

07:53.442 --> 08:01.442
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:24.550 --> 08:25.640
Stay right here.

08:25.641 --> 08:27.168
Stay right here, stay right here.

08:28.561 --> 08:36.561
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:45.452 --> 08:47.412
- [rattling]
- [gasps]

08:47.413 --> 08:48.879
Sean.

08:49.623 --> 08:51.074
Sean?

08:51.609 --> 08:59.609
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:30.831 --> 09:32.290
[snarling]

09:32.291 --> 09:33.578
Mary.

09:37.588 --> 09:38.547
Mary.

09:38.548 --> 09:42.300
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:42.301 --> 09:43.866
Sean!

09:44.451 --> 09:45.827
Sean!

09:50.606 --> 09:51.757
Sean!

09:52.561 --> 09:55.104
[snarling]

09:55.105 --> 09:59.025
[screams]

09:59.026 --> 10:02.885
[grunting]

10:06.533 --> 10:09.448
[screams]

10:11.872 --> 10:14.250
[panting]

10:14.708 --> 10:16.930
I got you, I got you. What happened?

10:19.713 --> 10:21.464
- No.
- Noodle.

10:21.465 --> 10:23.037
We have to go.

10:24.134 --> 10:26.469
<i>[intense music]</i>

10:26.470 --> 10:29.264
[snarling]

10:29.265 --> 10:37.265
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:39.483 --> 10:44.779
[snarling]

10:44.780 --> 10:52.780
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:04.174 --> 11:06.676
What exactly do you know about me?

11:06.677 --> 11:07.969
Can this wait?

11:07.970 --> 11:10.596
I'd like to die with a clean conscience.

11:10.597 --> 11:11.806
Good luck with that.

11:11.807 --> 11:14.600
Look, we all have files about us.

11:14.601 --> 11:16.503
You looked at my files?

11:18.022 --> 11:21.899
[both panting]

11:21.900 --> 11:23.109
Did she get you anywhere?

11:23.110 --> 11:24.902
I don't know. No.

11:24.903 --> 11:27.341
- What happened to your knee?
- That's not my blood.

11:29.867 --> 11:31.101
Noodle.

11:31.869 --> 11:33.476
[sighs]

11:33.501 --> 11:34.757
It's okay.

11:35.039 --> 11:36.640
It's okay.

11:39.460 --> 11:42.003
Will you please, please stop talking?

11:42.004 --> 11:43.796
Will you just tell me what you know?

11:43.797 --> 11:45.673
Look, we've all done things
we shouldn't.

11:45.674 --> 11:47.258
Sometimes they land us in detention.

11:47.259 --> 11:49.469
Sometimes they should land us in jai.

11:49.470 --> 11:50.803
I've never been to jail.

11:50.804 --> 11:52.513
Lucky you, thief.

11:52.980 --> 11:56.559
Look, whatever you found out,
it's not what you think.

11:56.675 --> 11:58.540
You feel guilty. I get that.

11:59.080 --> 12:00.289
But your nagging conscience

12:00.314 --> 12:01.814
is embedded deep in your brain,

12:01.815 --> 12:04.567
and your brain is about
to get ripped out by a freak.

12:04.568 --> 12:06.785
So for the love of God...

12:07.488 --> 12:09.238
Noodle's dead.

12:09.239 --> 12:11.574
Mary's still loose. We tried.

12:11.575 --> 12:13.034
Where?

12:13.035 --> 12:15.950
The gym lockers, three minutes ago.

12:16.497 --> 12:18.012
Shit. Where's Grover?

12:18.624 --> 12:21.667
<i>[gentle music]</i>

12:21.668 --> 12:22.835
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:22.836 --> 12:24.176
Mary.

12:30.010 --> 12:32.011
[snarls]

12:32.012 --> 12:35.014
<i>[intense music]</i>

12:35.015 --> 12:43.015
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:45.317 --> 12:50.196
[grunting]

12:50.197 --> 12:56.577
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:56.578 --> 13:04.578
[grunting, snarling]

13:18.661 --> 13:20.393
Let's consider the calculus.

13:20.394 --> 13:21.561
Calculus?

13:21.562 --> 13:22.895
That thing killed Noodle.

13:22.896 --> 13:24.689
It ripped him up and it drank his blood.

13:24.690 --> 13:26.732
- It has to die.
- I'll do it. Move.

13:26.733 --> 13:27.790
No, no, no!

13:27.815 --> 13:30.056
You are not killing her.

13:30.612 --> 13:32.280
That is my sister in there.

13:32.281 --> 13:34.699
That thing? It killed my best friend.

13:34.700 --> 13:36.951
That thing is Mary Jones.

13:36.952 --> 13:40.121
She loves Harry Potter,
and she's afraid of heights,

13:40.122 --> 13:42.582
and I swear to you she's
still in there somewhere.

13:42.583 --> 13:45.233
Look at her. She's suffering.

13:46.003 --> 13:49.151
For all we know, she could
get better, right?

13:49.822 --> 13:52.425
- They-they all could get better.
- I'm not about to find out.

13:52.426 --> 13:53.759
Grover has a point.

13:53.760 --> 13:55.595
We know very little about this disease.

13:55.596 --> 13:57.180
If we keep this thing alive,

13:57.181 --> 13:58.764
we can learn how to defend ourselves.

13:58.765 --> 14:00.016
Don't listen to him.

14:00.017 --> 14:01.934
- Just...
- Okay, yeah, sure, kill it.

14:01.935 --> 14:03.644
We can always find another one later.

14:03.645 --> 14:05.548
How hard can that be?

14:07.858 --> 14:09.859
You lie to us again,

14:09.860 --> 14:11.483
I'm gonna kill you both.

14:14.740 --> 14:18.242
[wind whistling]

14:18.243 --> 14:21.287
<i>[tense music]</i>

14:21.288 --> 14:29.288
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:36.178 --> 14:39.180
<i>[gentle music]</i>

14:39.181 --> 14:47.181
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:05.457 --> 15:06.833
Hey.

15:08.231 --> 15:10.059
How you holding up?

15:11.546 --> 15:13.320
I've been better.

15:14.773 --> 15:16.945
This whole thing's my fault.

15:18.483 --> 15:21.141
Trust me, it's not.

15:21.765 --> 15:23.857
I couldn't protect her.

15:24.851 --> 15:27.052
Stop beating yourself up.

15:27.380 --> 15:29.474
You did everything you could.

15:30.857 --> 15:32.569
Do you really believe that?

15:33.735 --> 15:35.210
Yeah.

15:39.825 --> 15:41.870
Do you think she'll ever come back?

15:44.037 --> 15:52.037
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:59.344 --> 16:07.344
[snarling]

16:14.526 --> 16:17.571
<i>[tense music]</i>

16:22.659 --> 16:23.701
[radio static]

16:23.702 --> 16:24.744
MAN: Keyword?

16:24.745 --> 16:26.329
Flashpoint Zulu.

16:26.330 --> 16:28.061
Who are you talking to?

16:29.207 --> 16:31.042
Um, myself.

16:31.043 --> 16:32.644
I'm starting to lose my mind.

16:33.272 --> 16:35.342
Hmm. I came in here to say thanks.

16:35.662 --> 16:38.013
You did the right thing,
keeping her alive.

16:39.154 --> 16:40.582
You mean the most useful thing,

16:40.607 --> 16:42.561
and you're not here to thank me.

16:43.305 --> 16:45.931
It's amazing what you can learn
with a few hours of static

16:45.956 --> 16:48.608
and nothing but student files.

16:55.120 --> 16:57.610
So I stole. Big whoop.

16:57.611 --> 16:59.779
Mm, chemicals.

16:59.780 --> 17:02.573
And not the kind you make
soap and candles with.

17:02.574 --> 17:04.794
Rust and aluminum powder.

17:05.702 --> 17:08.419
For ceramics. It was a glaze.

17:08.789 --> 17:11.624
Very combustible glaze.

17:11.625 --> 17:12.958
Burns right through metal.

17:12.959 --> 17:14.813
What type of art are you doing?

17:15.170 --> 17:16.628
May I take a stab?

17:17.031 --> 17:19.570
I think you used the chemicals
to make a thermite bomb.

17:20.509 --> 17:22.259
Doesn't prove anything.

17:22.984 --> 17:24.136
Not on its own.

17:24.137 --> 17:26.555
However, only a few days
after you stole the chemicals,

17:26.556 --> 17:29.266
there's a catastrophic fire
at the chemical plant.

17:29.267 --> 17:31.143
Quite the coincidence.

17:31.144 --> 17:33.479
And what are you suggesting?

17:33.480 --> 17:34.980
Nothing.

17:34.981 --> 17:37.149
Only that you might
have been responsible

17:37.150 --> 17:38.874
for the entire disaster.

17:39.736 --> 17:40.874
Bite me.

17:41.731 --> 17:43.857
We all have our crosses to bear.

17:43.882 --> 17:45.933
Maybe one day you'll tell me yours.

17:49.058 --> 17:52.015
You didn't have to trick me.

17:52.040 --> 17:53.749
Yeah? What should I have done?

17:53.750 --> 17:55.376
You could have said, "Hey,
there's a freak on the loose,

17:55.377 --> 17:57.586
and I'm doing this for your own good."

17:57.587 --> 17:59.825
Yeah, okay, like that would have worked.

18:02.217 --> 18:04.093
You're about to sleep there.

18:04.094 --> 18:05.845
Don't you tuck yourself in?

18:06.710 --> 18:08.514
No, I don't like feeling trapped.

18:08.851 --> 18:10.683
Well, for me, a bed needs to be made.

18:10.684 --> 18:12.518
Yeah, but you don't have
to pull up the blanket.

18:12.519 --> 18:16.313
[stammers indistinctly]

18:16.314 --> 18:17.640
All right.

18:23.739 --> 18:26.824
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

18:26.825 --> 18:34.825
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:45.051 --> 18:47.219
[snarling]

18:47.220 --> 18:55.220
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:00.901 --> 19:02.464
- What did you do to her?
- Hey!

19:02.489 --> 19:04.069
You tell me right now
what you've done to her.

19:04.070 --> 19:05.905
Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, hold up.

19:05.906 --> 19:07.072
What'd he do?

19:07.073 --> 19:09.033
He's torturing my sister!

19:09.034 --> 19:10.534
Okay, I am studying her.

19:10.535 --> 19:12.077
Don't lie to me. You're burning her.

19:12.078 --> 19:14.622
Hey, I never burned her.
It was just a test.

19:14.623 --> 19:16.123
And it turns out, I was right.

19:16.124 --> 19:17.416
They're afraid of fire.

19:17.417 --> 19:19.155
So now we have a weapon against freaks.

19:19.180 --> 19:20.598
Son of a bitch...

19:20.623 --> 19:24.725
We kept your sister alive
so we could survive.

19:27.124 --> 19:29.261
Show of hands, who thinks
I'm doing the right thing?

19:29.262 --> 19:31.316
Doing the right thing
would have been killing her.

19:36.370 --> 19:37.953
Tie vote.

19:39.564 --> 19:40.733
Violet?

19:44.736 --> 19:45.936
What are you waiting for?

19:47.427 --> 19:49.413
Violet, she's still my sister.

19:49.647 --> 19:50.950
I mean, she's a human being.

19:50.951 --> 19:54.203
Think of it as the greatest
good for the greatest number.

19:54.204 --> 19:56.288
What is most useful?

19:56.289 --> 19:57.706
Violet.

19:57.707 --> 19:59.252
I can't do this.

20:00.252 --> 20:02.266
We all have our crosses to bear.

20:08.802 --> 20:11.804
Raise your hand,
and we keep studying her.

20:11.805 --> 20:12.805
Violet.

20:13.658 --> 20:20.622
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:20.647 --> 20:22.078
I'm sorry, Grover.

20:41.670 --> 20:44.123
How could you side with that asshole?

20:45.309 --> 20:47.059
Barrett has a point.

20:47.084 --> 20:49.633
The more we know about
how this disease works...

20:49.634 --> 20:50.910
